{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "The UK to lead the effort to resettle Afghans fleeing the Taliban",
        "additional_details": "We are watching in shock as the Taliban retake control of Afghanistan. Afghans find themselves in a terrifying reality. Humanitarian crisis is imminent. A rush to get British nationals out - but what of civilians? Their amazing commitment to British forces in developing their country came with personal risk - now they are Taliban targets. Educated girls face an unimaginable future. There was trust between Britain and the Afghan people - we have a responsibility to help them.",
        "background": "The UK Government to spearhead international efforts, working with NATO countries and others, to provide routes for safe passage and asylum for Afghan civilians who need to escape the Taliban.",
